.Sh NAME
.
.Nm VisiData
.Nd a terminal utility for exploring and arranging tabular data
.
.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.
.Bl -inset -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact
.It Ic vd
.Op <options>
<input> ...
.
.It <command>
.Sy | vd
.Op <options>


.Sh Ns Sy "  replay mode" No
.It Ic vd
.Op <options>
.Sy Fl -play No <cmdlog>
.Op Fl -batch
.Op Fl d No <delay>
.Op Fl o No <output>
.Sy -- No
.Op Fl "-<field>=<value> ..."
.El

.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm VisiData
.No is a multipurpose tool for exploring, cleaning, editing, and restructuring data (see Sx SUPPORTED SOURCES Ns ).
.No Rows can be selected, filtered, and grouped; columns can be rearranged, transformed, and derived via regex or Python expressions; workflows can be saved, documented, and replayed via the Sx Commandlog Ns .
.Nm VisiData No is built on the
.Sy vdtui No platform.
.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact
.
.It Fl f, -filetype Ns = Ns Ar filetype
uses loader for
.Ar filetype
.No (see Sy SUPPORTED SOURCES Ns )
instead of file extension
.
.It Fl y, -confirm-overwrite Ns =F
overwrites existing files without confirmation 
.El

.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
.It See also Sx MINOR OPTIONS Ns .
.El
.
.Sh REPLAY MODE
.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact
.It Fl "p, --play" Ar cmdlog No
.No replays a saved Ar cmdlog No within the interface
.
.Bl -inset -offset xxxx -compact
.No Python format strings in the Ar cmdlog No (like \&"{ Ns Ar field Ns }\&") No are replaced with the Ar value No given on the command line.  These format options must be specified after Sy -- Ns .
.
.El
.It Fl "d, --delay" Ar seconds
.No waits Ar seconds No between commands
.
.It Fl "b, --batch"
replays in batch mode (with no interface and all status sent to stdout)
.
.It Fl "o, --output" Ar file No
.No saves the final visible sheet to Ar file No (as .tsv) at the end of the replay

.It Sy Commands During Replay
.El
.Bl -tag -width XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX -compact -offset XXX
.It Sy ^U
pauses/resumes replay
.It Sy Space
executes next row in the replaying sheet
.El
.
