.Sh CONFIG FILE
At the start of every session,
.Nm VisiData No looks for, in order, Sy .visidatarc No in the current directory, Sy $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/visidata/config Ns , or Sy $HOME/.visidatarc Ns , and calls Python exec() on its contents.  For example:
.Bd -literal
   options.min_memory_mb=100  # stop processing without 100MB free

   globalCommand('0', 'gh')   # alias '0' to move to first column, like vim

   aggregator('median', lambda values: sorted(values)[len(values)/2])
.Ed

